column14: After reviewing the file, I discovered that the measurement did NOT have a 0.88 velocity coefficient applied to all the surface velocities.  Therefore M1 is the original file that measred 31.2 cms, and the M1R file is the altered file that has 30.3 cms.  Discharge was not supposed to be this low. Probably should have waded the river, instead of using the cableway.
